"As a huge fan of Syrah, this one piqued my interest.  When colder, at a ""proper"" IPA temperature, the dryness supplied by the Syrah grapes is a bit overpowering. Allow to warm to near room temperature and this one becomes quite nice.  Pours a beautiful light ruby with light, white head that retains a ring around the glass even while warming and sitting for quite a long time.  Overall a nice, crisp - finishing surprise."
