"This is like a sparkling wine with the body and sweetness profile of a malty beer. The color is what you'd get if you poured a couple ounces of dark red wine into a light amber beer. The aroma is more red wine than beer. It's not hoppy like the 'IPA' on the label would suggest and neither is the taste. It has some of the taste characteristics common among DFH beers and has a similar mouthfeel. It's an interesting beer for the sake of being different, but I'm not sure that crossing beer and wine works for me."
