"Interesting taste combo. The hops are more citrus in the taste, and an earthy yet juicy grape flavor is here, slightly medicinal. There is also a bready malt presence that balances out this unorthodox brew in a well-done way I'd only expect from DFH. The grape must makes certain it is the defining aspect of this beer. Medium body and ample carbonation; a little sticky, and a little dry finishing due to some astringency. I didnt focus on this being an IPA whatsoever while reviewing this, the main reason being the brewery selected this as a year-round affair. Works for me. Aged cheddar with cracker going great with it too (as it would with grape wine). For what this creation is, it certainly lives up to its name. Other reviewers' impressions of this beer seem to express a loss to ""categorize"" it, but for me, I feel DFH succeeded once again in pushing the boundaries."
